    "Methodology and StrategyFor this investigation, an evaluation consisting of 126 multiple-choice questions pertinent to mechanical engineering program with a focus on mechanics was formulated by a ground of seasoned experts in the field.",
    "This assessment covers six distinct domains: Fluid Mechanics, with 16 questions; Mechanics of Vibration, 20 questions; Engineering Statics and Dynamics, 24 questions; Mechanics of Materials, 25 questions; Theory of Elasticity, 19 questions; and Continuum Mechanics, 22 questions.",
    "The specific questions featured in this examination are comprehensively detailed in Supplemental Material.",
    "Question designAs illustrated in Supplemental Material, the majority of the questions in the assessment predominantly focus on definitions and factual knowledge, alongside a considerable number of calculation-based questions.",
